manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Team Up. Fight On. AORUS, a premium gaming brand powered by GIGABYTE, delivers a full spectrum of gaming products ranging from gaming laptops, motherboards, graphics cards, mechanical gaming keyboards, to many other gaming hardware and gears, offering the most extreme gaming experiences for enthusiasts worldwide! Z390 AORUS ELITE AORUS Z390 motherboards are designed with thermals and speed in mind, ensuring users can best take advantage of Intel 9th generation processors. The AORUS and GIGABYTE Z390 series is loaded with a variety of premium feature sets and each board provides a sweet spot in performance and value. Assemble your next PC with AORUS and start with a strong foundation as each motherboard is built with Ultra Durable materials. Supports Intel 8th & 9th Gen Core i9/i7/i5/i3, Celeron, and Pentium Processors Dual Channel Non-ECC Unbuffered DDR4, 4 DIMMs 12+1 Phases Digital VRM Solution with DrMOS Advanced Thermal Design with Screw Mounted Heatsinks ALC1220-VB Enhance 114dB(Rear)/ 110dB(Front) SNR in Microphone RGB Fusion with Multi-Zone LED Light Show Design Smart Fan 5 with Hybrid Fan Headers with FAN STOP Dual M.2 with Single Thermal Guard

Unique Features Enhanced VRM Design The Z390 AORUS ELITE uses a 12*+1 phases digital CPU power design and has additional 8+4 Solid-pin CPU Power Connectors that allows enthusiasts to get the absolute maximum performance from the new 9th Gen Intel Core processors. RGB Fusion The onboard Digital LED's shine beautifully against the Z390 motherboard's monochrome pallet. Paint your system with bold colors with full RGB support and a redesigned RGB Fusion application, which gives the user complete control over the LEDs which surround the motherboard. Smart Fan 5 With Smart Fan 5 users can ensure that their gaming PC can maintain its performance while staying cool. Smart Fan 5 allows users to interchange their fan headers to reflect different thermal sensors at different locations on the motherboard and gives users up-to-the-second details on flow rate and temperatures.

Unique Features M.2 Thermal Guard With durability in mind, GIGABYTE provides a thermal solution for M.2 SSD devices. The M.2 Thermal Guard prevents throttling and bottlenecks from high speed M.2 SSDs as it helps to dissipate heat before it becomes an issue. Front USB Type-C Equipped with next generation connectivity, AORUS motherboards already support the chassis of the future. The onboard USB Type-C header for USB 3.1 Gen1 makes access convenient when connecting a USB 3.1 Gen1 drive or charging your new mobile device. AORUS 360 Armor AORUS motherboards are layered with Ultra Durable protection, such as an Integrated I/O shield, memory armor and PCIe armor, to give users a strong foundation to build their gaming systems.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 19, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This beast is amazing, but mind the power requirements!
reviews.reviewText: It does just about everything, and it does a great job. Key things to note:The motherboard's HDMI port has no integrated graphics to power it, so it's essentially useless. You'll need to plug things into whatever graphics card you purchase.It also needs quite a bit of power -- be sure you check the number of pins available on your power supply to make sure it can power the board's overall AND CPU requirements, plus whatever else you'll be connecting.Finally, the primary SSD connector is weirdly loose. You may want to use some sort of electronic-safe putty to secure the thermal plate, otherwise it jiggles for no real apparent reason.Tech support is typical of hardware manufacturers, which is to say almost nonexistent and requires making an account with Gigabyte to access at all. No surprises there.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Do NOT use a 120mm cpu fan. It will block a ddr4 memory slot.
reviews.reviewText: Thusfar, everything is working properly and I am satisfied with the performance. I hope this will remain the case and get the 4+ years service I got with the Z270. Aorus motherboards have proven to be very reliable and I depend on them to give me the most out of my gaming experiences.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 15, 2020
reviews.reviewText: not much to say other then its awesome. Bought a pre-built on FB and swapped this board into it, a i59600k, many more fans and RGBs and i love it. the BIOS is simple even for a 1st timer, had to switch the internal graphics so that i could run dual monitors, and it took me about 37 seconds haha. looks great, install was a breeze with some youtube clips.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2019
reviews.reviewText: Its a nice motherboard, works well. the BIOS looks clean. There is no Wifi with this board, I would reccomend getting a PCIE Wifi card or a Wifi USB stickI should see no issues with this. Its a great value for the money, if you wanted a comparable board from ASUS it would cost more.My biggest downfall with this product is installing the RGB software. There isnt as much in terms of lighting effects but it matches my ICUE profiles with a little bit of tinkering

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 7, 2023
reviews.reviewText: It kind of works, haven't hit any major issues with this motherboard, but the overall quality of the product feels very mediocre. This was the first time I bought Gigabyte so not sure if that's entirely expected, I would say that was worse than other motherboards that I had previously. I don't remember the exact details (I switched to another PC some time ago), but I remember that my general impression was "meh".

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Better than the Z390-Prime
reviews.reviewText: Got this Aorus Elite to replace a failed Asus Z390 Prime. The Prime board failed to enter the EFI bios after a while, and I didn’t want to wait on a replacement chip even though I have equipment and qualifications to solder one on. Shouldn’t have happened. This Gigabyte board is not only prettier as far as lighting and customization, but also the EFI bios has always been accessible and it hasn’t failed. The Prime had HDMI and DP for CPU graphics output, but this board only has HDMI (I know probably very few people actually want to run their dual displays on CPU graphics, but that’s what happens when you want to GPU mine). Overall I like this board. A lot.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars purchased New, but got a used one?
reviews.reviewText: i aquired this today, it said new when i purchased it but it came in used, i could see dust in a corner as it had been used, but reluctantly i installed it and sure enough it turned on for a second, glitched at post screen and then suddenly 2 pops, one from my psu and one from either the mb or my RTX 2080ti , I love Gigabyte products but, this time seeing it was NEW, it came in a open box style wraped in bubble wrap and only 2 packages of sata cables, nothing else no hardware or manual, worst i could easily tell it was USED/Refurbished as it wasnt cleaned fully.VERY disapointed now i have to order a new video card and power supply, boards getting refunded.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2019
reviews.reviewText: This motherboard has worked great for me so far. Has all the features one could look for in a gaming motherboard (tons of USB 3.0s, plenty of PCI space, etc). Wanted a good home for my i7 9900kf, and this has treated it great so far! Easy to get everything in my build installed in it, as well.

reviews.reviewTitle: Really good motherboard for the money!!
reviews.reviewText: This motherboard has got to be one of the best motherboards that I've ever seen, and especially for the price!! when I first got it, it looked so cool and there was not one bit of damage to the board or the box or anything after inspecting it really closely. Installing it was a breeze, and really easy compared to other motherboards that I'm after working with in the past. And last but not least it looks SO amazing when in use and even when it was in the box!! The only bad thing about it is that the gigabyte RGB fusion 2.0 software was really broken, but after some waiting it finally all loaded and I was able to change the color on it to blue to match my blue led strip and it looks so mint!!!But on my final note, highly recommended for anyone looking for a good bang for the buck option for their motherboard, and I also wanna do a small shout out to gigabyte for making it so perfect in looks, performance, and capability. Rock on guys, I hope that you all keep up the good work!!
Okay, But software looks so ancient ... .

reviews.reviewTitle: エントリーむけには最高
reviews.reviewText: これといった良いところがないが悪いところはないゲーミングエントリーとしては十分i9にも対応してるしm2は2機あるから拡張性も悪くないそしてオンボードオーディオもノイズのない綺麗な音、サウンドブラスターのサウンドボードを使ってるけど変わらないレベルにいいゲーミングエントリー、初自作で高スペにはコスパ最強ではないかな

reviews.reviewTitle: 高コストパフォーマンスなマザーボード
reviews.reviewText: i9-9900Kを使用しています。CPUは5Ghzにオーバークロックして常用していますが、問題なく動作しています。付属しているマニュアルもわかりやすいものなので、初心者の方でも安心して購入できる製品ではないでしょうか。UEFIもわかりやすく直感的に操作できます。M.2用のヒートシンクは一枚なので、2枚搭載予定の方は別途ヒートシンクを購入する必要があります。必要なものがきれいにまとまった製品でこの価格なので、コスパに優れていると思います。
Lo utilize como actualización, tenía el h365 de la serie básica de gigabyte, este arous sin duda es una excelente opción
